<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="49" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1101,1521]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1245,1269]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">Remarks.</emphasis>
The morphology of this specimen agrees well with the original description of the species and with that of the Mediterranean specimen, which has slightly longer tentacular and dorsal cirri. With this new record, the distribution of the species is extended to the north in the Tropical Eastern Pacific and constitutes the first record in the Mexican Pacific, which may mean that it is a widespread amphi-American species (
<bibRefCitation author="Fauchald" box="[1130,1309,1353,1377]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" refString="Fauchald, K. (1977) Polychaetes from Intertidal Areas in Panama, with a Review of Previous Shallow-Water Records. Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology, 221, 1 - 181." type="journal article" year="1977">
Fauchald, 
<number box="[1249,1309,1353,1377]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" value="1977.0">1977</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1101,1521]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,298,1389,1414]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">Habitat.</emphasis>
Algae, seaweeds, vermetid reefs, sediments (from coarse sand to mud), calcareous concretions (San Martín, 
<number box="[241,302,1425,1449]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49" value="2003.0">2003</number>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="49" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1101,1521]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,1461,1486]" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">Distribution.</emphasis>
Eastern Atlantic (from Galicia to Cape Green), Mediterranean Sea, Caribbean Sea (
<collectingCountry box="[1325,1386,1461,1485]" name="Cuba" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">Cuba</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[151,271,1497,1521]" name="Venezuela" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
), Pacific coasts of 
<collectingCountry box="[480,569,1498,1521]" name="Panama" pageId="2" pageNumber="49">Panama</collectingCountry>
and southern Mexican Pacific.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
